There’s no significant trend, no seasonality, and the data is stationary. Z-scores are within ±1.6, with no outliers flagged. Smoothing methods reveal no hidden spikes. No multivariate or spatial corroboration is present, and context thresholds remain within normal variability. Hence, I'll conclude it's normal. The summary will be concise, ideally around 130 words, and I won’t use heavy formatting. Now, I can produce the final JSON.</think>"'}}]}
